# The native iOS project is generated on demand (npx cap add ios) — it needs
# Xcode + CocoaPods, which are macOS-only, so it can't live in a Windows-authored
# commit the way android/ does. CI regenerates it each run. A Mac dev who wants
# to commit it (to pin native tweaks, as android/ is) can force-add and drop
# this line. See docs/Android_Dev.md / the ios-build CI job.
ios/
